OpenAI=E2=80=99s New Model
------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-09-12/openai-=
releases-o1-model-with-reasoning-capabilities ) :

OpenAI is releasing a new artificial intelligence model known internally as=
 =E2=80=9CStrawberry=E2=80=9D that can perform some human-like reasoning ta=
sks, as it looks to stay at the top of a crowded market of rivals. The new =
model, called o1 , is designed to spend more time computing the answer befo=
re responding to user queries, the company said in a blog post ( https://op=
enai.com/index/introducing-openai-o1-preview/ ) Thursday. With the model, O=
penAI=E2=80=99s tools should be able to solve multi-step problems, includin=
g complicated math and coding questions.

=E2=80=9CAs an early model, it doesn=E2=80=99t yet have many of the feature=
s that make ChatGPT useful, like browsing the web for information and uploa=
ding files and images,=E2=80=9D the company said. =E2=80=9CBut for complex =
reasoning tasks this is a significant advancement and represents a new leve=
l of AI capability. Given this, we are resetting the counter back to 1 and =
naming this series OpenAI o1.=E2=80=9D

I think this model is really interesting, and definitely a breakthrough; th=
ere are also a lot of unknowns as to exactly how it works, both in terms of=
 the model and in terms of the operational infrastructure necessary to supp=
ort it. With that in mind, consider this Update as my initial draft on how =
I am thinking about this model and what it means; I expect to update my thi=
nking as we get more understanding on how exactly it works.

For now, though, I thought the following example (inspired by Ethan Mollick=
 ( https://www.oneusefulthing.org/p/something-new-on-openais-strawberry ) )=
 is a great example of what this model is capable of: solving the New York =
Times Daily Mini crossword. Specifically, I chose last Saturday=E2=80=99s c=
rossword ( https://www.nytimes.com/crosswords/game/mini/2024/09/14 ) , whic=
h is a 7=C3=977 puzzle (the rest of the week is 5=C3=975). I=E2=80=99ll get=
 to why I chose Saturday in a moment, but here is the puzzle:

The Saturday, September 14, NYT mini crossword ( https://www.nytimes.com/cr=
osswords/game/mini/2024/09/14 )

o1 is text-only, so I needed to describe the puzzle; here was my prompt:

Solve this 7=C3=977 crossword puzzle

Row 1 has three blanks in columns 1 through 3
Row 2 has one blank in column 1
Row 3 has one blank in column 1
